==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dreissena
<hw>Dreis"se*na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
Named after <ets>Dreyssen</ets>, a Belgian physician.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of bivalve shells of which one species
(<spn>Dreissena polymorpha</spn>) is often so abundant as to be very
troublesome in the fresh waters of Europe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

